1. U.S. Citizenship
2. Obtain & maintain a Secret Security clearance
3. Education requirements: https://www.opm.gov/policy-data-oversight/classification-qualifications/general-schedule-qualification-standards/0500/auditing-series-0511/
4. Experience performing a variety of routine taskings in the areas of audit planning, research, scheduling, and coordination
5. Experience gathering and reviewing background information on organizations to be audited to develop an understanding of their programs, structures, policies, objectives, systems, and internal controls
...

1. This employer participates in E-Verify and will provide the federal government with your Form I-9 information to confirm that you are authorized to work in the U.S.; for more information about E-Verify, please go to www.dhs.gov/e-verify
2. Position requires employee to be fingerprinted and successfully pass a background investigation.
3. Education: For classifications where the Minimum Qualifications (MQs) are based on meeting education requirements only: If education is required to meet the MQs please attach a copy of all of your transcripts that show the completion of the required education.
4. Applicants who completed their education outside the United States (with foreign degrees/transcripts) must obtain and submit verification of United States course/degree equivalency by the time of appointment.
5. Foreign education credential evaluation services can be found at https://www.naces.org.
